# UI specifications

When working on console UI (header, modals, main view, layout, or any on-screen content):

1. **Read the format**: Canonical file is `specs/console-ui/format/spec.md` (`docs/ui-spec-format.md` is a stub).
2. **Read UI components**: Use [docs/ui-components.md](docs/ui-components.md) to understand which component is responsible for each part of the screen (title bar, header, modals, toolbar, visualizer area).
3. **Read existing specs**: Canonical UI specs live under `specs/console-ui/` (hub: `specs/console-ui/spec.md`). `docs/ui-spec-*.md` are stubs. Read the matching `specs/console-ui/<surface>/spec.md` so line numbers and descriptions stay accurate.
4. **Update or create specs when you change layout**:
   - Edit the matching `specs/console-ui/**/spec.md` (not the stub). Refresh the screenshot (from a screen dump per ADR-0046) and update the "Line reference" section so every line is listed and described.
   - New screens: add `specs/console-ui/<surface>/spec.md` following `specs/TEMPLATE.md` and link from `specs/console-ui/spec.md`.
5. **Generating screenshots**: Use the app’s screen dump (Print Screen or `--dump-after N` / `--dump-path`) to capture ASCII output; paste into the Screenshot block and then write the line reference for each line.

Do not complete console UI changes that affect what appears on screen without updating the relevant `specs/console-ui/**/spec.md` so the docs stay in sync with the implementation.
